1778646898644433	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxg0		item.update	bn-5kad	{"field":"description","value":"## Goal\n\nAudit and eliminate remaining Git CLI subprocess calls across maw, replacing local object/ref/worktree/status operations with maw-git/gix primitives wherever practical.\n\n## Validated inventory (2026-05-13, refreshed by bn-3471)\n\nSee `docs/git-subprocess-inventory.md` (checked in by bn-3471) for the full classified breakdown and recommended implementation order.\n\nCommand used: `rg 'Command::new\\(\"git\"\\)' -n crates src tests benches`.\n\nCurrent result: **543** matches total (was 522 at the 2026-05-01 snapshot).\n\n- 471 matches under `crates/`, `src/`, and `benches/` (was 453).\n- 72 matches under top-level `tests/` (was 69).\n- The 543 substring count includes 24 instances of the `StdCommand::new(\"git\")` alias spelling, which is the same shape of subprocess call.\n\nClassified breakdown:\n\n| Bucket | Calls |\n|---|---:|\n| Production replace-now (local ops) | **251** |\n| Production temporary remote carveout (push/fetch) | **8** |\n| Crate-local `#[cfg(test)]` fixture | 212 |\n| Top-level integration-test fixture | 71 |\n| Intentional git-compatibility assertion | 1 |\n\nThe 251 replace-now production count is the number to drive down. Carveouts (8) are pinned to push/fetch protocol calls and have a written DoD in the inventory document.\n\nTop current clusters (production-only count after splitting in-file tests):\n\n| Prod | File | Area |\n|---:|---|---|\n| 22 | `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/working_copy.rs` | dirty-work capture/replay |\n| 15 | `crates/maw-cli/src/init.rs` (renamed from `v2_init.rs`) | project init |\n| 14 | `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs` | merge engine surface |\n| 13 | `crates/maw-cli/src/changes/mod.rs` | change branch/PR workflow |\n| 9  | `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/recover.rs` | recovery show/search/restore |\n| 9  | `crates/maw-cli/src/push.rs` | push surface (2 carveouts excluded) |\n| 7  | `crates/maw-assurance/src/oracle.rs` | oracle observation |\n| 6  | `crates/maw-tui/src/app.rs` | TUI git queries |\n| 6  | `src/merge/quarantine.rs` | merge quarantine |\n| 5  | `src/merge/build_phase.rs` | merge build |\n| 5  | `crates/maw-core/src/backend/copy.rs` | backend copy |\n| 4  | `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/capture.rs` | snapshot capture |\n| 4  | `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/resolve_structured.rs` | resolve autocommit |\n| 4  | `crates/maw-core/src/backend/git.rs` | workspace backend |\n\nSeveral files previously listed (e.g., `crates/maw-core/src/oplog/write.rs`, `epoch_gc.rs`, `crates/maw-core/src/refs.rs`) have **zero production calls** — all their hits are in-file `#[cfg(test)]` fixtures. They are no longer replace-now work items.\n\n## Working assumptions\n\n- Push/fetch protocol calls remain permanent carveouts. DoD for a carveout is documented in `docs/git-subprocess-inventory.md`. There are 8 such calls; any future call matching the carveout shape must be added to that document or migrated.\n- Hot-path merge/rebase/capture/resolve work (Phase A in the inventory) has higher value than one-off init or test scaffolding.\n- The inventory now distinguishes production behavior from test setup. Progress is measured against the 251-call replace-now count, not against the 543 substring total.\n\n## Drift since 2026-05-01\n\n- `workspace/recover.rs` gained +4 calls (bn-sgm8 restore paths).\n- `src/merge/collect.rs` gained +6 calls (test fixtures from merge-engine work).\n- `crates/maw-cli/src/transport.rs` gained +2 in-file tests.\n- `crates/maw-cli/src/v2_init.rs` renamed to `init.rs` (commit 79208cb8); count unchanged.\n- No file dropped to zero production calls since the prior snapshot."}	blake3:CHeI2hcY-ZajBRXOlTP5wea7kK_rvs5S7vaHjSrz0PM
